
**DOCKER IMAGES COMMANDS**

1. docker images                           ---- to check images present in local
2. docker search images-name               ---- to seerch images on docker-hub
3. docker pull images-name                 ---- to pull images from docker-hub
4. docker rmi images-name                  ---- to delete images
5. docker images prune                     ---- to delete all unused images
6. docker tag old-images  new-images:v1    ---- to rename old images to new image
7. docker build -t images-name:v1  .       ---- to build images from docker file here v1 is tag for images  . MEANCE CURRENT DIRECTORY

**DOCKER CONTAINER COMMANDS**

8. docker ps                     ---- to check all runnig containers
9. docker ps -a                  ---- to check all stop container
10.docker start containe-name    ---- to start container
11.docker stop container         ---- to stop container
12.docker rm container-name      ---- to delete container
13.docker container prune        ---- to delet all unused container at a time
14.docker  attach container-name ---- to enter in container
      OR
15.docker exec -it contaier-name /bin/bash
16.docker run -it -d -p 8080:80 or P --name contaner-name image-name     ---- to make and run contaienr from images amd  p for assing port
                                                                           or P take random port.
17.systemctl status docker       ---- to check docker runnig or not
18.systemctl start/stop docker   ---- to start or stop docker                   
              

